Yes, it can still do **parallel uploads with chunks**.

But important distinction:

```text
Uppy + Tus
= resumable uploads + parallel files

Custom chunk controller
= resumable uploads + parallel files + parallel chunks
```

For what you want, I recommend:

```text
Use custom controller-based chunk upload.
Do not use Tus middleware for this part.
```

Your architecture should be:

```text
Frontend Blazor/MudBlazor
    |
    | calls API controller
    v
Backend UploadController
    |
    | media files
    v
On-prem temp folder
    |
    v
FFmpeg convert to WAV
    |
    v
Azure Blob Storage


Other files
    |
    v
Upload directly to Azure Blob Storage
```

## Correct flow for media files

```text
1. Frontend selects audio/video files

2. Frontend calls:
   POST /api/media-upload/start

3. Backend returns:
   uploadId
   chunkSize
   parallelUploadLimit

4. Frontend splits file into chunks

5. Frontend uploads 4, 5, or 6 chunks/files in parallel:
   POST /api/media-upload/chunk

6. Backend saves chunks to on-prem temp folder

7. Frontend calls:
   POST /api/media-upload/complete

8. Backend combines chunks into original file

9. Backend calls your FFmpeg service

10. Backend uploads WAV to Blob Storage
```

